See I started using this app because it was embedded in Verizon's message+ stock messaging. Photo studio was the only reason I was using vz message plus, it allowed seemles editing and it only took a few clicks to get from inside the messaging app to the photo studio editor and back to the messaging app. One day photo studio was no longer part of Verizon's message+. So I started my quest. I ended up dumping vzmessage+. Back to this app... One great feature in this app is the grid while editing as well as the ability to zoom while adding marks on the picture, or being able to scroll using 2 finger swipe. These seem so basic but I found no other app that did it like photo studio. Other apps do it but it takes more clicks to get around.  The biggest plus is that I now go from my preferred messaging app to photo studio and back to attaching the picture in almost the same amount of clicks as when it was embedded in vz message+. Actually a few more, but this is ok. If you used message plus and you miss photo studio like I did until now. Get photo studio pro well worth the 5 bucks , then  pair it up with Android messages and you will be very happy!!!.  To flow from on to the other include the messaging app album from within photo studio, then you will have direct access to pictures saved to this folder, u will be able to edit and share with a few clicks. !!!  Hope this was helpful;-)!
